  "title": "Initialize instantsearch.js with a hierarchicalFacetsRefinements parameter",
  "body": "Hi, \n\nI would like to retrieve a list of objects for a defined category. \n\nFor this I tested two methods:\n\n``` javascript\nvar search = instantsearch({\n    [...],\n    searchParameters: {\n      hierarchicalFacetsRefinements: {\n        'categories.fr.0': {\n          0: 'Revêtement > Éléments de décor > Poignées de portes'\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  });\n```\n\nThis returns me an error message: _Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'facets' of undefined_\n\n``` javascript\nvar search = instantsearch({\n    [...],\n    searchParameters: {\n      facetsRefinements: {\n        'categories.fr.0': {\n          0: 'Revêtement'\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  });\n```\n\nIt works just for a level 1 category .. In my case \"Revêtement\", then I want to pass it \"Revêtement > Éléments de décor > Poignées de portes\"\n\nHow to do ? An idea ?\n",
